cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is related to natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on sequence labeling for slot filling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes enhancements to LSTM-based models, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves modeling label dependencies and incorporating global information, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses the ATIS corpus, which is a dataset commonly used in NLP tasks such as named entity recognition and intent detection, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible category.
